CHRIS:
Hello?

82
00:16:15.473 --> 00:16:16.892
In here.

83
00:16:18.643 --> 00:16:20.770
Hi. How did your day go?
Oh, not too bad.

84
00:16:20.937 --> 00:16:24.232
It was like the, uh, Walt Disney version
of the Ho Chi Minh story.

85
00:16:24.399 --> 00:16:25.650
Other than that, terrific.

86
00:16:25.817 --> 00:16:28.445
What we got, anything exciting?
Here.

87
00:16:28.904 --> 00:16:31.156
Oh, all right.
And also, you got an invitation.

88
00:16:31.323 --> 00:16:33.867
What's this?
Dinner at the White House.

89
00:16:34.034 --> 00:16:36.286
You're kidding.
Is it a big party or something?

90
00:16:36.453 --> 00:16:37.746
I think it's five or six people.

91
00:16:37.913 --> 00:16:40.749
Oh. Thursday, huh? All right.

92
00:16:40.916 --> 00:16:41.958
REGAN:
Hi, Mom.

93
00:16:42.125 --> 00:16:43.960
CHRIS:
What'd you do today?

94
00:16:44.127 --> 00:16:45.795
Stuff.
What's that mean, stuff?

95
00:16:45.962 --> 00:16:49.799
Well, uh, me and Sharon played a game
in the backyard.

96
00:16:49.966 --> 00:16:52.302
You did.
And we had a picnic down by the river.

97
00:16:52.469 --> 00:16:54.304
CHRIS:
That sounds good.

98
00:16:54.471 --> 00:16:55.513
You should have seen.

99
00:16:55.680 --> 00:16:58.684
This man came along on this
beautiful gray horse.

100
00:16:58.851 --> 00:17:00.561
Really? What kind?
Wasn't he pretty?

101
00:17:00.728 --> 00:17:02.813
Was it a mare, a gelding, what?

102
00:17:02.980 --> 00:17:05.024
I think it was a gelding.
Mm-hm.

103
00:17:05.191 --> 00:17:07.818
It was gray. Oh, it was so beautiful.

104
00:17:07.985 --> 00:17:10.237
The guy let me ride it all around
and everything.

105
00:17:10.404 --> 00:17:12.444
You're kidding.
SHARON: She rode for half an hour.

106
00:17:12.573 --> 00:17:17.495
It was so nice. Oh, I loved it.
Oh, Mom, can't we get a horse?

107
00:17:17.662 --> 00:17:21.040
Not while we're in Washington, honey.
Why not, Mom? Ha, ha.

108
00:17:21.207 --> 00:17:23.042
We'll see when we get home, okay?

109
00:17:23.209 --> 00:17:25.836
When could I have one?
We'll see, Regan. We'll see.

110
00:17:26.003 --> 00:17:29.215
Hey, listen, on the party invitations,
I wanted to write a personal...

111
00:17:29.382 --> 00:17:32.134
Regan, don't! Regan, come back here!
Ha-ha-ha.

112
00:17:33.386 --> 00:17:35.554
[BOTH LAUGHING]

113
00:17:36.681 --> 00:17:39.226
CHRIS: All right, give it up. Give it up!
REGAN: No!

114
00:17:39.393 --> 00:17:41.353
CHRIS: Ooh!
REGAN: Ha-ha-ha.

115
00:17:41.520 --> 00:17:43.146
You'll be sorry! Come on.
No!

116
00:18:14.094 --> 00:18:15.429
MAN:
Father?

117
00:18:15.595 --> 00:18:18.056
Could you help an old altar boy?

118
00:18:18.223 --> 00:18:19.267
I'm a Catholic.

119
00:18:42.373 --> 00:18:44.459
BOY 1:
All right, come on, man.

120
00:18:45.126 --> 00:18:46.846
BOY 2: What, are you crazy?
BOY 1: Go ahead.

121
00:18:47.003 --> 00:18:49.964
[BOYS SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

122
00:19:19.495 --> 00:19:21.455
[PEOPLE SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY ON RADIO]

123
00:19:45.939 --> 00:19:47.524
Mama?

124
00:19:57.700 --> 00:19:59.327
Mama?

125
00:20:00.411 --> 00:20:01.704
Mama?

126
00:20:02.789 --> 00:20:05.875
Dimmy! Dimmy!

127
00:20:06.042 --> 00:20:08.461
[SPEAKING IN GREEK]

128
00:20:09.671 --> 00:20:11.214
Oh, how are you, Mama?

129
00:20:11.381 --> 00:20:13.550
I'm so glad to see you.
You look good.

130
00:20:13.716 --> 00:20:15.426
I'm all right.

131
00:20:15.593 --> 00:20:18.054
How's your leg?
How about you? You are all right?

132
00:20:18.221 --> 00:20:19.556
I'm fine, Mama. I'm fine.

133
00:20:19.722 --> 00:20:21.766
[MAN SPEAKING IN GREEK ON RADIO]

134
00:20:24.687 --> 00:20:27.815
Your Uncle John passed by to visit me.

135
00:20:27.982 --> 00:20:30.317
KARRAS: Oh, really? When?
Last month.

136
00:20:34.905 --> 00:20:37.241
Too tight?
No.

137
00:20:38.200 --> 00:20:42.329
You have to stay off it. You can't go
up and down the stairs. You have to give it a rest.

138
00:20:42.496 --> 00:20:43.914
Okay.

139
00:20:51.505 --> 00:20:53.257
[SIGHS]

140
00:20:54.216 --> 00:20:57.845
I could take you somewhere where
you'd be safe. You wouldn't be alone.

141
00:20:58.012 --> 00:21:01.807
There would be people around. You wouldn't
be sitting here listening to a radio.

142
00:21:01.974 --> 00:21:03.977
[SPEAKING IN GREEK]

143
00:21:06.521 --> 00:21:07.814
You understand me?

144
00:21:07.981 --> 00:21:12.694
This is my house
and I'm not going no place.

145
00:21:21.494 --> 00:21:22.913
[COUGHS]

146
00:21:25.665 --> 00:21:27.792
Dimmy, you worry for something?

147
00:21:27.959 --> 00:21:29.961
No, Mama.
You are not happy?

148
00:21:30.128 --> 00:21:31.880
Tell me, what is the matter?

149
00:21:32.047 --> 00:21:35.217
Mama, I'm all right. I'm fine.
Really, I am.

150
00:21:51.484 --> 00:21:53.486
[GREEK MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO]

151
00:22:09.460 --> 00:22:10.920
Here it comes.

152
00:22:11.087 --> 00:22:12.421
There.

153
00:22:12.588 --> 00:22:13.839
[BOTH LAUGHING]

154
00:22:15.591 --> 00:22:17.031
Oh, look at that.
Do you like it?

155
00:22:17.093 --> 00:22:19.845
Aw, isn't that funny? Ha, ha.

156
00:22:20.471 --> 00:22:23.683
I better put him over here to dry, though.
He's still wet.

157
00:22:23.849 --> 00:22:26.143
Oh, here we go.

158
00:22:26.895 --> 00:22:28.855
There, he can dry there.

159
00:22:29.022 --> 00:22:31.191
Hey, where'd this come from?

160
00:22:32.359 --> 00:22:34.778
I found it.
Where?

161
00:22:36.238 --> 00:22:37.531
Closet.

162
00:22:38.699 --> 00:22:40.075
Huh.

163
00:22:40.284 --> 00:22:41.868
You been playing with it?

164
00:22:42.035 --> 00:22:44.037
Yup.
Do you know how?

165
00:22:44.204 --> 00:22:46.039
I'll show you.

166
00:22:50.168 --> 00:22:51.712
Wait a minute. You need two.

167
00:22:51.878 --> 00:22:55.173
No, you don't. I do it all the time.

168
00:22:55.340 --> 00:22:57.551
Oh, yeah? Well, let's both play with it.

169
00:23:00.012 --> 00:23:01.888
You really don't want me to play, huh?

170
00:23:02.055 --> 00:23:05.267
No, I do. Captain Howdy said no.

171
00:23:05.434 --> 00:23:08.396
Captain who?
Captain Howdy.

172
00:23:08.563 --> 00:23:10.064
Who's Captain Howdy?

173
00:23:10.231 --> 00:23:13.943
You know. I make the questions
and he does the answers.

174
00:23:14.110 --> 00:23:17.780
Oh, Captain Howdy. Yeah, I see.
He's nice.

175
00:23:17.947 --> 00:23:19.907
Oh, I'll bet he is.

176
00:23:20.074 --> 00:23:22.910
Here, I'll show you.
All right.

177
00:23:23.077 --> 00:23:27.081
Captain Howdy,
do you think my mom's pretty?

178
00:23:29.042 --> 00:23:31.044
Captain Howdy?

179
00:23:31.210 --> 00:23:33.296
Captain Howdy, that isn't very nice.

180
00:23:33.463 --> 00:23:35.965
Well, maybe he's sleeping.
You think?

181
00:23:38.009 --> 00:23:40.845
Regan, why are you reading that stuff?

182
00:23:41.012 --> 00:23:42.263
Because I like it.

183
00:23:42.430 --> 00:23:45.183
It's not even a good picture of you.
Look at that.

184
00:23:45.350 --> 00:23:47.935
You look so mature.
I wouldn't talk.

185
00:23:48.102 --> 00:23:51.106
You wouldn't talk?
Well, I didn't know they were taking it.

186
00:23:51.273 --> 00:23:53.275
I didn't have my makeup man there.

187
00:23:53.609 --> 00:23:56.111
Let me take an eyelash off your face.

188
00:23:56.278 --> 00:23:58.447
Okay. No, I didn't get it.

189
00:23:58.781 --> 00:24:00.866
Mm.
What are we gonna do on your birthday?

190
00:24:01.033 --> 00:24:03.911
Isn't it nice it's on Sunday this year?

191
00:24:04.078 --> 00:24:06.205
No work? What can we do?

192
00:24:06.372 --> 00:24:07.414
I don't know.

193
00:24:07.581 --> 00:24:08.861
Well, what would you like to do?

194
00:24:08.999 --> 00:24:10.918
Got any ideas?
Mm-mm.

195
00:24:11.085 --> 00:24:12.753
Hmm?

196
00:24:13.045 --> 00:24:15.756
Let me think. Let me think.
What can we do?

197
00:24:15.923 --> 00:24:18.634
Hey, we never finished seeing
all the sights in Washington.

198
00:24:18.801 --> 00:24:21.136
Didn't get to Lee Mansion
and lots of stuff.

199
00:24:21.303 --> 00:24:24.807
Shall we do that? Go sightseeing?
If it's a nice day?

200
00:24:24.973 --> 00:24:27.101
Yeah, let's do that.
Okay.

201
00:24:27.518 --> 00:24:32.690
And tomorrow night,
I'll take you to a movie. Okay?

202
00:24:32.857 --> 00:24:34.776
Oh, I love you.

203
00:24:34.943 --> 00:24:37.487
I love you, Rags.

204
00:24:38.863 --> 00:24:39.906
[REGAN GIGGLES]

205
00:24:40.073 --> 00:24:41.199
We'll have a good day, yeah?

206
00:24:41.658 --> 00:24:44.285
You can bring Mr. Dennings, if you like.

207
00:24:44.452 --> 00:24:46.079
Mr. Dennings?

208
00:24:46.246 --> 00:24:48.331
Well, you know, it's okay.

209
00:24:48.498 --> 00:24:49.791
Well, thank you very much...

210
00:24:49.958 --> 00:24:52.961
but why on earth would I wanna bring
Burke on your birthday?

211
00:24:53.128 --> 00:24:54.671
Well, you like him.

212
00:24:54.838 --> 00:24:58.800
Yeah, I like him. Don't you like him?
Hey, what's going on? What is this?

213
00:24:58.967 --> 00:25:02.470
You're gonna marry him, aren't you?
Oh, my God. Are you kidding?

214
00:25:02.637 --> 00:25:04.305
What?
Me marry Burke Dennings?

215
00:25:04.472 --> 00:25:06.599
Don't be silly. Of course not.

216
00:25:06.766 --> 00:25:08.685
Where did you ever get an idea like that?

217
00:25:08.852 --> 00:25:10.854
But you like him.

218
00:25:11.020 --> 00:25:14.859
Of course I like him. I like pizzas too,
but I'm not gonna marry one.

219
00:25:15.025 --> 00:25:17.278
You don't like him like Daddy?

220
00:25:18.446 --> 00:25:20.698
Regan, I love your daddy.

221
00:25:20.865 --> 00:25:23.117
I'll always love your daddy, honey.

222
00:25:23.534 --> 00:25:26.871
Okay? Burke just comes
around here a lot, because...

223
00:25:27.288 --> 00:25:28.330
[SIGHS]

224
00:25:28.497 --> 00:25:30.708
Well, he's lonely.
He don't got nothing to do.

225
00:25:30.875 --> 00:25:33.961
Well, I heard differently.

226
00:25:34.128 --> 00:25:36.464
Oh, you did? What did you hear, huh?

227
00:25:36.630 --> 00:25:39.383
I don't know. I just thought.
Come on. What did you hear?

228
00:25:39.550 --> 00:25:41.218
Well, you didn't think so good.

229
00:25:41.385 --> 00:25:43.596
How do you know? Ha, ha.
Ha-ha-ha.

230
00:25:43.762 --> 00:25:46.432
Because Burke and I are just friends.
Okay? Really.

231
00:25:46.599 --> 00:25:47.725
Okay.

232
00:25:48.100 --> 00:25:50.144
You ready for sleep?

233
00:25:52.271 --> 00:25:54.983
Good night.
Good night, honey.

234
00:25:55.400 --> 00:25:59.696
