Lord, I was born a ramblin' man</i>

235
00:26:00.572 --> 00:26:05.410
<i>Lord, I was born a ramblin' man</i>

236
00:26:06.244 --> 00:26:08.246
[CROWD CHATTERING]

237
00:26:15.587 --> 00:26:17.631
KARRAS:
It's my mother, Tom.

238
00:26:18.089 --> 00:26:20.800
She's alone. I never should have left her.

239
00:26:22.260 --> 00:26:25.263
At least in New York, I'd be near her.
I'd be close to her.

240
00:26:25.430 --> 00:26:28.099
I could see about a transfer, Damien.

241
00:26:29.809 --> 00:26:34.524
I need reassignment, Tom. I want out of
this job. It's wrong, it's no good.

242
00:26:34.690 --> 00:26:36.776
You're the best we've got.

243
00:26:37.652 --> 00:26:39.654
