01:06:24.468 --> 01:06:27.347
I don't know anyone who fits
that description.

751
01:06:28.890 --> 01:06:30.392
Ah.

752
01:06:32.060 --> 01:06:34.646
Doctor's ethics.
If you knew, you wouldn't tell, huh?

753
01:06:34.813 --> 01:06:35.981
No, I probably wouldn't.

754
01:06:36.606 --> 01:06:39.526
Not to bother you with trivia,
but a psychiatrist...

755
01:06:39.693 --> 01:06:42.529
in sunny California, no less...

756
01:06:42.696 --> 01:06:47.158
was put in jail for not telling
the police what he knew about a patient.

757
01:06:47.826 --> 01:06:52.122
Is that a threat?
No, I mention it only in passing.

758
01:06:53.748 --> 01:06:55.834
Incidentally,
I mention it only in passing...

759
01:06:56.001 --> 01:06:59.087
I could always tell the judge it was
a matter of confession.

760
01:07:00.839 --> 01:07:02.757
[CHUCKLING]

761
01:07:02.924 --> 01:07:05.176
Hey, Father, wait a minute.

762
01:07:05.343 --> 01:07:07.262
Do you like movies?
Very much.

763
01:07:07.429 --> 01:07:10.474
Well, I get passes
to the best shows in town.

764
01:07:10.641 --> 01:07:14.603
Mrs. K, though, you know,
she gets tired, never likes to go.

765
01:07:14.770 --> 01:07:16.897
That's too bad.
Yeah, I hate to go alone.

766
01:07:17.064 --> 01:07:19.567
I love to talk film...

767
01:07:19.734 --> 01:07:23.154
discuss, to critique.

768
01:07:23.320 --> 01:07:28.492
You want to see a film with me?
I got passes to the Crest. It's Othello.

769
01:07:28.659 --> 01:07:30.494
Who's in it?
Who's in it?

770
01:07:30.661 --> 01:07:34.623
Debbie Reynolds, Desdemona,
and Othello, Groucho Marx. You happy?

771
01:07:34.790 --> 01:07:36.792
I've seen it.
Ah.

772
01:07:37.126 --> 01:07:40.838
One last time. You can think
of some priest who fits the bill?

773
01:07:41.005 --> 01:07:45.301
Come on.
No, answer the question, Father Paranoia.

774
01:07:46.469 --> 01:07:49.138
All right. All right.

775
01:07:50.098 --> 01:07:52.642
You know who I think really did it?
Who?

776
01:07:52.809 --> 01:07:54.644
The Dominicans. Go pick on them.

777
01:07:55.395 --> 01:07:57.898
I could have you deported,
you know that?

778
01:08:00.025 --> 01:08:01.234
I lied.

779
01:08:02.652 --> 01:08:04.488
You look like Sal Mineo.

780
01:08:08.825 --> 01:08:12.245
BARRINGER: It looks like a type of disorder
that's, uh, rarely ever seen anymore...

781
01:08:12.412 --> 01:08:14.498
except in primitive cultures.

782
01:08:14.873 --> 01:08:19.002
We call it, uh,
somnambular-form possession.

783
01:08:19.628 --> 01:08:22.339
Quite frankly, we really don't know
much about it at all...

784
01:08:22.506 --> 01:08:26.843
except that it starts with a conflict
or a guilt...

785
01:08:27.010 --> 01:08:30.806
and it leads to the patient's delusions
that his body has been invaded...

786
01:08:30.973 --> 01:08:34.811
by some alien intelligence. Um...

787
01:08:34.977 --> 01:08:36.145
A spirit, if you will.

788
01:08:36.312 --> 01:08:39.816
Look, I'm telling you again,
and you'd better believe me...

789
01:08:39.982 --> 01:08:42.819
I am not going to lock her up
in some goddamn asylum.

790
01:08:42.985 --> 01:08:45.655
Well, it's out of.
And I don't care what you call it.

791
01:08:45.822 --> 01:08:47.532
I'm not putting her away.

792
01:08:47.698 --> 01:08:49.200
Well, I'm sorry.

793
01:08:49.367 --> 01:08:51.202
You're sorry? Jesus Christ!

794
01:08:51.369 --> 01:08:56.082
Eighty-eight doctors, and all you can
tell me with all your bullshit is...

795
01:09:12.933 --> 01:09:17.729
Of course, there is one outside chance
for a cure.

796
01:09:18.522 --> 01:09:24.361
But, um, I think of it
as a shock treatment.

797
01:09:25.362 --> 01:09:27.322
As I said, it's a very outside chance...

798
01:09:27.489 --> 01:09:30.159
Would you just name it, for God's sakes?
What is it?

799
01:09:30.325 --> 01:09:32.828
Do you have any religious beliefs?
CHRIS: No.

800
01:09:32.995 --> 01:09:35.414
What about your daughter?

801
01:09:35.581 --> 01:09:37.374
No. Why?

802
01:09:37.583 --> 01:09:39.251
Have you ever heard of exorcism?

803
01:09:41.712 --> 01:09:44.423
Well, it's a stylized ritual...

804
01:09:44.590 --> 01:09:51.180
in which the, uh, rabbi or the priest try
to drive out the so-called invading spirit.

805
01:09:51.346 --> 01:09:53.433
It's been pretty much discarded
these days...

806
01:09:53.600 --> 01:09:58.354
except by the Catholics, who keep it
in the closet as a sort of embarrassment.

807
01:09:58.563 --> 01:10:01.608
But it, uh, has worked, in fact...

808
01:10:01.774 --> 01:10:04.694
although not for the reasons they think,
of course.

809
01:10:04.861 --> 01:10:08.615
It's purely force of suggestion.

810
01:10:08.781 --> 01:10:13.578
The, uh-The victim's belief in possession
is what helped cause it...

811
01:10:13.745 --> 01:10:15.371
so in that same way...

812
01:10:15.538 --> 01:10:18.791
the belief in the power of exorcism
can make it disappear.

813
01:10:21.169 --> 01:10:25.215
You're telling me that I should
take my daughter to a witch doctor.

814
01:10:26.132 --> 01:10:27.592
Is that it?

815
01:12:06.319 --> 01:12:07.945
Karl?

816
01:12:09.238 --> 01:12:11.741
Did you put this in Regan's bedroom?

817
01:12:14.452 --> 01:12:16.412
She's going to be well?

818
01:12:17.621 --> 01:12:22.043
Karl, if you put this in Regan's bedroom,
I want you to tell me. Now, did you?

819
01:12:22.209 --> 01:12:24.879
No, not me.

820
01:12:25.046 --> 01:12:26.088
I didn't.

821
01:12:44.274 --> 01:12:47.611
This was under Regan's pillow.
Did you put it there?

822
01:12:47.986 --> 01:12:49.404
Of course, I didn't.

823
01:12:50.989 --> 01:12:52.199
I didn't put it.

824
01:12:52.366 --> 01:12:53.825
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

825
01:12:53.992 --> 01:12:56.411
KARL: Excuse me, madam.
What?

826
01:12:57.454 --> 01:12:59.623
A man to see you.
CHRIS: What man?

827
01:13:06.213 --> 01:13:08.590
KINDERMAN:
Might your daughter remember, perhaps...

828
01:13:08.757 --> 01:13:11.760
if Mr. Dennings was in her room
that night?

829
01:13:13.220 --> 01:13:15.138
Why do you ask?
Mm.

830
01:13:15.555 --> 01:13:17.391
Might she remember?

831
01:13:19.559 --> 01:13:22.855
No, she was heavily sedated.

832
01:13:23.356 --> 01:13:24.816
It's serious?

833
01:13:25.650 --> 01:13:27.276
Yes, I'm afraid it is.

834
01:13:28.736 --> 01:13:31.197
May I ask...?
We still don't know.

835
01:13:32.156 --> 01:13:33.741
Watch out for drafts.

836
01:13:33.908 --> 01:13:39.330
A draft in the fall when the house is hot
is a magic carpet for bacteria.

837
01:13:39.497 --> 01:13:41.290
Excuse me, madam. Anything else?

838
01:13:41.457 --> 01:13:43.584
No, Karl, we're fine. Thank you.

839
01:13:44.168 --> 01:13:45.962
It's all right, Karl.

840
01:13:50.174 --> 01:13:51.801
Why are you asking all this?

841
01:13:51.968 --> 01:13:53.344
It's strange.

842
01:13:54.595 --> 01:13:59.016
The deceased comes to visit,
stays only 20 minutes...

843
01:13:59.183 --> 01:14:03.355
and leaves all alone a very sick girl.

844
01:14:04.815 --> 01:14:06.608
And speaking plainly, Mrs. MacNeil...

845
01:14:06.775 --> 01:14:11.905
it isn't likely he would fall
from a window.

846
01:14:12.531 --> 01:14:15.451
Besides, a fall wouldn't do to his neck
what we found.

847
01:14:15.617 --> 01:14:18.454
Except maybe one chance in a thousand.

848
01:14:18.996 --> 01:14:21.248
No. My hunch...

849
01:14:21.540 --> 01:14:24.793
My opinion...

850
01:14:24.960 --> 01:14:28.964
he was killed by a very powerful man:
point one.

851
01:14:30.299 --> 01:14:32.801
And the fracturing
of his skull: point two...

852
01:14:32.968 --> 01:14:35.721
plus the various other things
we mentioned...

853
01:14:36.972 --> 01:14:39.850
would make it very probable...

854
01:14:40.017 --> 01:14:42.812
probable, not certain...

855
01:14:43.438 --> 01:14:49.235
that the deceased was killed and
then pushed from your daughter's window.

856
01:14:49.402 --> 01:14:53.990
But nobody was in the room
except your daughter, so how can this be?

857
01:14:57.827 --> 01:15:00.163
It could be one way.

858
01:15:00.538 --> 01:15:03.458
If someone came calling
between the time Miss Spencer left...

859
01:15:03.625 --> 01:15:05.793
and the time you returned.

860
01:15:05.960 --> 01:15:08.463
Judas Priest, just a second.

861
01:15:09.464 --> 01:15:12.550
The servants? They have visitors?
Not at all.

862
01:15:12.717 --> 01:15:15.261
You were expecting a package that day,
some delivery?

863
01:15:15.428 --> 01:15:16.638
Not that I know of.

864
01:15:16.804 --> 01:15:19.474
Groceries, cleaning, uh, a package?

865
01:15:19.641 --> 01:15:22.352
I really wouldn't know.
See, Karl takes care of all that.

866
01:15:24.438 --> 01:15:25.731
I see.

867
01:15:25.898 --> 01:15:27.858
Would you like to ask him?

868
01:15:28.734 --> 01:15:31.195
No, never mind, it's...

869
01:15:32.530 --> 01:15:34.865
It's very remote.

870
01:15:35.574 --> 01:15:38.118
No, never mind.

871
01:15:38.619 --> 01:15:40.162
Yeah.

872
01:15:48.671 --> 01:15:50.631
Would you like some more coffee?

873
01:15:51.298 --> 01:15:52.967
Please.

874
01:16:19.077 --> 01:16:20.620
[CHUCKLES]

875
01:16:27.919 --> 01:16:29.337
That's cute.

876
01:16:30.589 --> 01:16:32.841
Your daughter, she's the artist?

877
01:16:35.135 --> 01:16:37.178
Thank you.
You're welcome.

878
01:16:37.846 --> 01:16:39.681
Incidentally, um...

879
01:16:40.724 --> 01:16:42.517
you might ask your daughter...

880
01:16:42.684 --> 01:16:46.022
if she remembers seeing Mr. Dennings
in her room that night.

881
01:16:46.188 --> 01:16:49.525
Look, he wouldn't have any reason
in the world to go up to her room.

882
01:16:49.692 --> 01:16:52.778
Oh, I know, I realize...

883
01:16:53.112 --> 01:16:56.449
but if certain British doctors never
asked, "What is this fungus?"...

884
01:16:56.616 --> 01:16:59.827
we wouldn't today have penicillin.
Correct?

885
01:17:00.077 --> 01:17:03.664
Well, when she's better, I'll ask her.

886
01:17:03.831 --> 01:17:06.459
Yeah, couldn't hurt.
Okay.

887
01:17:06.626 --> 01:17:09.045
Uh, in the meantime...

888
01:17:10.546 --> 01:17:11.881
That's okay.

889
01:17:12.048 --> 01:17:16.218
I really hate to ask you this, but...
What?

890
01:17:16.719 --> 01:17:20.556
For my daughter,
could you please give an autograph?

891
01:17:20.723 --> 01:17:23.100
Of course. Uh, where's a pencil?

892
01:17:23.267 --> 01:17:25.102
Right here. Here.

893
01:17:25.686 --> 01:17:26.979
Oh.

894
01:17:27.356 --> 01:17:28.565
She'd love it.

895
01:17:30.192 --> 01:17:31.735
And what's her name?

896
01:17:34.279 --> 01:17:36.531
I lied. It's for me.

897
01:17:36.698 --> 01:17:38.158
[CHRIS CHUCKLES]

898
01:17:38.325 --> 01:17:42.371
The spelling is on the back: Kinderman.
Okay.

899
01:17:42.788 --> 01:17:45.957
You know that film you made, um, Angel?

900
01:17:46.124 --> 01:17:48.543
Oh, yeah.
I saw that six times.

901
01:17:48.710 --> 01:17:50.921
Really?
It was beautiful.

902
01:17:51.338 --> 01:17:53.882
Ha, ha. Thank you.

903
01:17:56.551 --> 01:17:59.721
You're a very nice lady.

904
01:18:01.973 --> 01:18:04.309
Thank you.
You're a nice man.

905
01:18:05.268 --> 01:18:08.480
Uh, I'll come back
when she's feeling better.

906
01:18:12.276 --> 01:18:14.112
Bye.
Bye.

907
01:18:34.966 --> 01:18:36.926
REGAN:
Please, no!

908
01:18:37.093 --> 01:18:39.178
DEMONIC VOICE: Do it!
REGAN: Please, don't!

909
01:18:39.345 --> 01:18:42.724
DEMONIC VOICE:
You bitch! Do it! Do it!

910
01:18:42.890 --> 01:18:44.475
REGAN:
Please, no!

911
01:18:44.642 --> 01:18:46.811
[SCREAMING]

912
01:18:46.978 --> 01:18:50.065
REGAN [IN DEMONIC VOICE]:
Yes! Let Jesus fuck you!

913
01:18:50.232 --> 01:18:53.152
Let Jesus fuck you! Let him fuck you!

914
01:18:53.318 --> 01:18:55.404
[BOTH GRUNTING]

915
01:18:57.448 --> 01:18:58.490
Aah!

916
01:18:58.657 --> 01:19:01.493
Give it! Give it to me! Aah!

917
01:19:02.202 --> 01:19:05.664
Ugh!
Lick me! Lick me!

918
01:19:05.831 --> 01:19:07.458
[COUGHS]

919
01:19:07.624 --> 01:19:08.876
[GRUNTS]

920
01:19:09.042 --> 01:19:10.461
[SCREAMS]

921
01:19:11.170 --> 01:19:12.254
SHARON:
Chris!

922
01:19:13.881 --> 01:19:16.967
Mrs. MacNeil, open the door!

923
01:19:22.639 --> 01:19:24.099
[BANGING ON DOOR]

924
01:19:24.266 --> 01:19:25.517
Open the door!

925
01:19:25.684 --> 01:19:28.145
[AS BURKE]
Do you know what she did...

926
01:19:28.312 --> 01:19:30.355
your cunting daughter?

927
01:19:30.773 --> 01:19:32.358
[SCREAMING]

928
01:19:50.376 --> 01:19:52.003
Chris MacNeil?

929
01:19:52.337 --> 01:19:53.379
Please, go away.

930
01:19:53.546 --> 01:19:55.632
I'm Father Karras.

931
01:19:57.550 --> 01:19:59.427
I'm very sorry. Hello.

932
01:19:59.594 --> 01:20:01.930
I should have told you
I wouldn't be in uniform.

933
01:20:02.096 --> 01:20:03.681
Yeah, that would have helped.

934
01:20:03.848 --> 01:20:06.226
Have you got a cigarette, Father?
Sure.

935
01:20:10.230 --> 01:20:11.397
Thanks.

936
01:20:23.577 --> 01:20:24.912
Cold.

937
01:20:25.079 --> 01:20:26.247
Yeah.

938
01:20:28.123 --> 01:20:29.583
Uh...

939
01:20:30.751 --> 01:20:33.212
How did a shrink ever get to be a priest?

940
01:20:33.379 --> 01:20:36.340
It's the other way around. The Society
sent me through medical school.

941
01:20:36.507 --> 01:20:37.633
Oh.

942
01:20:37.800 --> 01:20:39.134
Where?

943
01:20:40.052 --> 01:20:43.556
Harvard, Bellevue, Johns Hopkins.

944
01:20:43.722 --> 01:20:46.100
Places like that.
I see.

945
01:20:47.977 --> 01:20:50.938
You're a friend of Father Dyer's, right?
Yes, I am.

946
01:20:51.105 --> 01:20:53.482
Pretty close?
Pretty close.

947
01:20:53.650 --> 01:20:55.527
Did he talk to you about my party?

948
01:20:55.694 --> 01:20:57.279
He sure did.

949
01:20:57.821 --> 01:20:59.364
About my daughter?

950
01:20:59.531 --> 01:21:01.324
No, I didn't know you had one.

951
01:21:03.618 --> 01:21:06.162
He didn't mention her?
No.

952
01:21:06.329 --> 01:21:07.956
Oh.

953
01:21:08.415 --> 01:21:10.625
Didn't tell you what she did?

954
01:21:10.792 --> 01:21:12.669
He didn't mention her.

955
01:21:14.296 --> 01:21:16.715
Priests are pretty tight-mouthed,
then, huh?

956
01:21:16.882 --> 01:21:18.884
That depends.

957
01:21:19.175 --> 01:21:21.177
On what?
The priest.

958
01:21:21.970 --> 01:21:23.430
Sure.

959
01:21:24.931 --> 01:21:28.560
I mean, what if a person,
uh, came to you...

960
01:21:28.727 --> 01:21:31.980
you know, that was a murderer
or criminal of some kind...

961
01:21:32.147 --> 01:21:35.401
and they wanted some kind of help?

962
01:21:35.568 --> 01:21:37.570
I mean, would you have to turn him in?

963
01:21:37.737 --> 01:21:40.781
Well, if he came to me
for spiritual advice, I'd say no.

964
01:21:40.948 --> 01:21:42.909
You wouldn't?
No, I wouldn't.

965
01:21:43.451 --> 01:21:45.536
But I would try to convince him
to turn himself in.

966
01:21:45.703 --> 01:21:47.163
Mm-hm.

967
01:21:47.538 --> 01:21:51.626
And, uh, how do you go about
getting an exorcism?

968
01:21:55.880 --> 01:21:57.381
I beg your pardon?

969
01:22:00.843 --> 01:22:06.390
If, um-If a person's, you know,
possessed by a demon, or something...

970
01:22:06.557 --> 01:22:08.976
how do they get an exorcism?

971
01:22:09.685 --> 01:22:13.648
I'd have to get them into a time machine
and get them back to the 16th century.

972
01:22:13.814 --> 01:22:15.483
I didn't get you.

973
01:22:15.650 --> 01:22:17.861
It just doesn't happen anymore,
Mrs. MacNeil.

974
01:22:18.028 --> 01:22:19.738
Oh, yeah? Since when?

975
01:22:21.031 --> 01:22:24.993
Well, since we learned about mental
illness, paranoia, schizophrenia.

976
01:22:25.160 --> 01:22:27.120
All those things they taught me
at Harvard.

977
01:22:27.287 --> 01:22:29.957
Mrs. MacNeil,
since the day I joined the Jesuits...

978
01:22:30.123 --> 01:22:33.877
I've never met one priest
who has performed an exorcism. Not one.

979
01:22:35.295 --> 01:22:37.172
Yeah, well...

980
01:22:37.923 --> 01:22:39.466
[CLEARS THROAT]

981
01:22:39.633 --> 01:22:43.428
It just so happens that somebody
very close to me...

982
01:22:43.887 --> 01:22:45.555
is probably possessed.

983
01:22:46.556 --> 01:22:48.266
And needs an exorcist.

984
01:22:48.725 --> 01:22:51.561
Father Karras, it's my little girl.

985
01:22:51.728 --> 01:22:52.938
[SOBS]

986
01:22:53.105 --> 01:22:55.357
Then that's all the more reason
to forget about exorcism.

987
01:22:55.524 --> 01:22:56.775
Why? I don't understand.

988
01:22:56.942 --> 01:22:59.654
To begin with, it could make things worse.
Oh, how?

989
01:22:59.821 --> 01:23:02.073
Secondly, the Church,
before it approves an exorcism...

990
01:23:02.240 --> 01:23:05.451
conducts an investigation to see if
it's warranted. That takes time.

991
01:23:05.618 --> 01:23:07.258
Yeah, but...
Meanwhile, your daughter.

992
01:23:07.328 --> 01:23:10.039
You could do it yourself.
No. I'd need Church approval...

993
01:23:10.206 --> 01:23:13.042
and that's rarely given.
But... Uh...

994
01:23:15.086 --> 01:23:16.671
Could you see her?
Yes, I could.

995
01:23:16.838 --> 01:23:18.558
I could see her as a psychiatrist, but I...

996
01:23:18.715 --> 01:23:21.050
Oh, not a psychiatrist. She needs a priest.

997
01:23:21.217 --> 01:23:24.887
She's seen every fucking psychiatrist
in the world, and they sent me to you.

998
01:23:25.054 --> 01:23:26.806
Now are you gonna send me
back to them?

999
01:23:26.973 --> 01:23:29.851
Jesus Christ, won't somebody help me?
You don't understand...

1000
01:23:30.018 --> 01:23:33.104
Oh, God, can't you help her?
Just help her!

1001
01:23:33.271 --> 01:23:35.273
[CRYING]

1002
01:23:46.910 --> 01:23:49.913
[REGAN GROANING]

1003
01:24:04.136 --> 01:24:05.888
It wants no straps.

1004
01:24:21.529 --> 01:24:22.864
KARRAS:
Hello, Regan.

1005
01:24:26.451 --> 01:24:29.287
I'm a friend of your mother's.
I'd like to help you.

1006
01:24:29.996 --> 01:24:32.373
[IN DEMONIC VOICE]
You might loosen these straps, then.

1007
01:24:33.333 --> 01:24:35.668
I'm afraid you might hurt yourself,
Regan.

1008
01:24:36.377 --> 01:24:38.505
I'm not Regan.

1009
01:24:39.339 --> 01:24:40.632
I see.

1010
01:24:45.553 --> 01:24:48.473
Well, then, let's introduce ourselves.
I'm Damien Karras.

1011
01:24:48.681 --> 01:24:50.266
And I'm the devil.

1012
01:24:50.433 --> 01:24:52.352
Now, kindly undo these straps.

1013
01:24:53.019 --> 01:24:55.605
If you're the devil,
why not make the straps disappear?

1014
01:24:55.772 --> 01:24:58.942
That's much too vulgar a display
of power, Karras.

1015
01:25:00.401 --> 01:25:01.737
Where's Regan?

1016
01:25:02.029 --> 01:25:03.864
In here, with us.

1017
01:25:06.075 --> 01:25:08.327
Show me Regan
and I'll loosen one of the straps.

1018
01:25:09.245 --> 01:25:12.123
[AS OLD MAN]
Could you help an old altar boy, Father?

1019
01:25:13.082 --> 01:25:15.459
[IN DEMONIC VOICE]
Your mother's in here with us, Karras.

1020
01:25:15.626 --> 01:25:17.711
Would you like to leave a message?

1021
01:25:17.878 --> 01:25:20.131
I'll see that she gets it.

1022
01:25:25.511 --> 01:25:27.054
If that's true...

1023
01:25:29.598 --> 01:25:32.476
then you must know my mother's
maiden name.

1024
01:25:34.061 --> 01:25:35.312
What is it?

1025
01:25:43.363 --> 01:25:44.406
What is it?

1026
01:25:44.573 --> 01:25:45.615
[ROARS]

1027
01:25:45.782 --> 01:25:47.159
[YELLS]

1028
01:25:47.325 --> 01:25:49.578
[COUGHING]

1029
01:26:38.961 --> 01:26:40.463
Thank you.

1030
01:26:42.965 --> 01:26:47.803
Look, I'm only against the possibility of
doing your daughter more harm than good.

1031
01:26:48.221 --> 01:26:51.307
Nothing you could do
could make it any worse.

1032
01:26:51.849 --> 01:26:53.517
I can't do it.

1033
01:26:54.143 --> 01:26:56.270
I need evidence that the Church
would accept...

1034
01:26:56.437 --> 01:26:58.314
as signs of possession.
Like what?

1035
01:26:58.481 --> 01:27:00.900
Speaking in a language
she's never known or studied.

1036
01:27:01.067 --> 01:27:02.401
What else?

1037
01:27:03.653 --> 01:27:06.990
I don't know. I'd have to look it up.

1038
01:27:07.157 --> 01:27:09.534
I thought you were supposed
to be an expert.

1039
01:27:10.410 --> 01:27:12.329
There are no experts.

1040
01:27:13.163 --> 01:27:16.625
You probably know as much about
possession as most priests.

1041
01:27:17.209 --> 01:27:19.503
Look, your daughter doesn't say
she's a demon.

1042
01:27:19.670 --> 01:27:22.047
She says she's the devil himself.

1043
01:27:22.214 --> 01:27:24.341
If you've seen as many psychotics
as I have...

1044
01:27:24.508 --> 01:27:28.178
you'd realize that's the same thing
as saying you're Napoleon Bonaparte.

1045
01:27:29.388 --> 01:27:33.976
You asked me what I think is best
for your daughter.

1046
01:27:34.851 --> 01:27:40.607
Six months under observation
in the best hospital you can find.

1047
01:27:43.235 --> 01:27:45.320
You show me Regan's double...

1048
01:27:45.487 --> 01:27:49.575
same face, same voice, everything...

1049
01:27:49.742 --> 01:27:51.786
and I'd know it wasn't Regan.

1050
01:27:52.704 --> 01:27:54.289
I'd know in my gut.

1051
01:27:55.707 --> 01:27:59.294
I'm telling you that that thing upstairs
isn't my daughter.

1052
01:28:00.003 --> 01:28:02.422
I want you to tell me that you know
for a fact...

1053
01:28:02.588 --> 01:28:05.675
that there's nothing wrong
with my daughter except in her mind.

1054
01:28:05.842 --> 01:28:08.886
Tell me you know for a fact
that an exorcism wouldn't do any good.

1055
01:28:09.053 --> 01:28:11.014
You tell me that!

1056
01:28:22.567 --> 01:28:25.445
Did Regan know a priest was
coming over?

1057
01:28:26.904 --> 01:28:30.034
No.
Did you know my mother died recently?

1058
01:28:30.743 --> 01:28:33.245
Yes, I did. I'm very sorry.
No.

1059
01:28:33.912 --> 01:28:35.581
Is Regan aware of it?

1060
01:28:36.957 --> 01:28:38.250
Not at all.

1061
01:28:39.752 --> 01:28:41.086
Why do you ask?

1062
01:28:42.921 --> 01:28:44.923
It's not important. Good night.

1063
01:29:11.576 --> 01:29:13.578
REGAN [ON RECORDER]:
Hello?

1064
01:29:13.745 --> 01:29:15.789
[CHRIS SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
ON RECORDER]

1065
01:29:15.955 --> 01:29:20.251
<i>CHRIS: Here, take it and just don't...
REGAN: Okay. Um.</i>

1066
01:29:20.418 --> 01:29:21.878
<i>Hello, Daddy?</i>

1067
01:29:22.045 --> 01:29:23.630
<i>This is me.</i>

1068
01:29:24.422 --> 01:29:27.550
<i>What should I say? I don't know.
CHRIS: Just talk to your daddy.</i>

1069
01:29:27.717 --> 01:29:30.053
<i>Anything you want.
REGAN: All right, um...</i>

1070
01:29:30.220 --> 01:29:34.933
<i>CHRIS: Tell him what you've been doing
and how you're feeling and like that.</i>

1071
01:29:36.434 --> 01:29:37.685
REGAN:
Uh...

1072
01:29:37.852 --> 01:29:40.313
<i>Well, you see, um...</i>

1073
01:29:40.730 --> 01:29:43.817
<i>I mean, I hope you can hear me.
Can you hear me okay?</i>

1074
01:29:43.983 --> 01:29:46.223
<i>Well, uh, let me see.
CHRIS: He's not gonna answer you.</i>

1075
01:29:46.319 --> 01:29:48.405
REGAN:
Uh, ha-ha-ha.

1076
01:29:48.571 --> 01:29:50.908
<i>CHRIS: Go on. Talk to your daddy, honey.
REGAN: Um...</i>

1077
01:29:51.075 --> 01:29:53.411
<i>I don't know what to say, though. Um...</i>

1078
01:29:53.869 --> 01:29:57.164
<i>Well, let's see. First we... No.</i>

1079
01:29:57.540 --> 01:30:00.668
<i>Wait. I don't know.
CHRIS: Come on, Regan.</i>

1080
01:30:00.835 --> 01:30:02.837
<i>Tell him about Washington.
REGAN: Okay.</i>

1081
01:30:03.003 --> 01:30:05.840
<i>See, we're in Washington now,
Daddy, and...</i>

1082
01:30:08.134 --> 01:30:11.720
He broke the bread,
gave it to his disciples and said:

1083
01:30:14.515 --> 01:30:17.059
"Take this, all of you, and eat it...

1084
01:30:20.896 --> 01:30:22.189
for this is my body."

1085
01:30:28.904 --> 01:30:31.825
When the supper was ended,
he took the cup.

1086
01:30:32.284 --> 01:30:35.245
Again he gave you thanks and praise.

1087
01:30:35.871 --> 01:30:39.249
He gave the cup to his disciples and said,
"Take this...

1088
01:30:39.583 --> 01:30:41.960
all of you, and drink from it.

1089
01:30:45.338 --> 01:30:47.924
This is the cup of my blood.

1090
01:30:49.426 --> 01:30:53.513
The blood of the new and everlasting
covenant, the mystery of faith."

1091
01:30:54.806 --> 01:30:57.225
[IN DEMONIC VOICE]
What an excellent day for an exorcism.

1092
01:30:59.394 --> 01:31:00.604
You'd like that?

1093
01:31:00.770 --> 01:31:02.689
Intensely.

1094
01:31:03.565 --> 01:31:05.942
But wouldn't that drive you
out of Regan?

1095
01:31:06.109 --> 01:31:08.361
It would bring us together.

1096
01:31:09.738 --> 01:31:10.947
You and Regan?

1097
01:31:11.114 --> 01:31:12.825
You and us.

1098
01:31:14.535 --> 01:31:17.121
[MOANS]

1099
01:31:24.086 --> 01:31:28.007
Did you do that?
Uh-huh.

1100
01:31:32.929 --> 01:31:34.931
Do it again.
In time.

1101
01:31:35.097 --> 01:31:36.682
No, now.

1102
01:31:36.849 --> 01:31:38.601
In time.

1103
01:31:39.644 --> 01:31:43.022
Mirabile dictu, don't you agree?

1104
01:31:44.524 --> 01:31:45.775
You speak Latin?

1105
01:31:46.108 --> 01:31:51.113
[BOTH SPEAKING IN LATIN]

1106
01:31:51.739 --> 01:31:52.782
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

1107
01:31:52.949 --> 01:31:54.451
[SPEAKS IN LATIN]

1108
01:31:54.618 --> 01:31:56.578
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

1109
01:31:56.745 --> 01:31:59.039
How long are you planning
to stay in Regan?

1110
01:31:59.581 --> 01:32:02.084
Until she rots and lies stinking
in the earth.

1111
01:32:05.212 --> 01:32:06.338
What's that?

1112
01:32:06.880 --> 01:32:08.549
Holy water.

1113
01:32:09.925 --> 01:32:11.468
You keep it away.

1114
01:32:13.136 --> 01:32:14.638
[SCREAMS]

1115
01:32:14.805 --> 01:32:16.807
It burns!

1116
01:32:16.974 --> 01:32:19.476
Oh, it burns!

1117
01:32:19.643 --> 01:32:22.271
[SCREAMING]

1118
01:32:24.314 --> 01:32:26.608
[SPEAKING GIBBERISH]

1119
01:32:27.442 --> 01:32:28.944
[GROWLS]

1120
01:32:29.111 --> 01:32:31.405
[CONTINUES SPEAKING GIBBERISH]

1121
01:32:42.250 --> 01:32:43.585
Who are you?

1122
01:32:50.341 --> 01:32:54.345
[SCREAMING]

1123
01:32:55.972 --> 01:32:59.142
CHRIS:
You know, I'm, like, in seclusion.

1124
01:33:02.854 --> 01:33:05.315
No, I'm just exhausted from work.

1125
01:33:07.650 --> 01:33:09.068
Um...

1126
01:33:09.527 --> 01:33:11.863
She's... She's all right.

1127
01:33:12.030 --> 01:33:13.906
She's just a little...

1128
01:33:16.702 --> 01:33:18.495
I don't want to talk about it, okay?

1129
01:33:21.373 --> 01:33:23.167
Um...

1130
01:33:23.459 --> 01:33:27.713
Okay, I'll talk to you. I'll call you
as soon as it's over, all right?

1131
01:33:29.048 --> 01:33:31.425
No, I just... I'm really...
I'm going through something...

1132
01:33:31.592 --> 01:33:33.510
and I just have to, uh...

1133
01:33:34.553 --> 01:33:36.221
No, no. No, no.

1134
01:33:36.472 --> 01:33:38.349
There's nothing.

1135
01:33:39.141 --> 01:33:40.809
Hey, thanks a lot.

1136
01:33:41.560 --> 01:33:43.062
Bye, now.

1137
01:33:57.117 --> 01:33:59.371
Want a drink?
Please.

1138
01:34:00.080 --> 01:34:01.414
What do you drink?

1139
01:34:01.581 --> 01:34:03.166
Uh, Scotch.

1140
01:34:04.584 --> 01:34:07.879
Ice, water.
Okay.

1141
01:34:13.551 --> 01:34:15.720
No ice. I'll get some from the kitchen.

1142
01:34:15.929 --> 01:34:17.529
No, I'll take it straight.
It's fine.

1143
01:34:17.597 --> 01:34:18.598
No, please, sit.

1144
01:34:18.765 --> 01:34:20.725
Really? You sure?
Yeah, sit.

1145
01:34:32.278 --> 01:34:33.905
Where's her father?

1146
01:34:34.072 --> 01:34:35.281
In Europe.

1147
01:34:35.448 --> 01:34:37.283
Have you told him what's happening?
No.

1148
01:34:37.450 --> 01:34:39.745
Well, I think you should.

1149
01:34:47.336 --> 01:34:52.633
I told Regan that was holy water. I sprinkled
it on her and she reacted very violently.

1150
01:34:54.552 --> 01:34:55.803
It's tap water.

1151
01:34:55.970 --> 01:34:57.054
What's the difference?

1152
01:34:57.221 --> 01:35:01.976
Holy water's blessed. And that doesn't
help support a case for possession.

1153
01:35:12.445 --> 01:35:15.906
She killed Burke Dennings.

1154
01:35:16.073 --> 01:35:17.283
What?

1155
01:35:20.996 --> 01:35:23.039
She killed Burke Dennings.

1156
01:35:24.666 --> 01:35:27.502
She pushed him out her window.

1157
01:35:30.630 --> 01:35:33.508
[REGAN SPEAKING GIBBERISH
ON RECORDER]

1158
01:35:41.183 --> 01:35:42.267
<i>KARRAS:
Who are you?</i>

1159
01:35:42.434 --> 01:35:45.270
[REGAN CONTINUES
SPEAKING GIBBERISH]

1160
01:35:45.437 --> 01:35:47.898
It's a language, all right. It's English.

1161
01:35:49.357 --> 01:35:50.484
What do you mean?

1162
01:35:50.650 --> 01:35:52.861
It's English in reverse. Listen.

1163
01:35:53.528 --> 01:35:55.280
DEMONIC VOICE:
Give us time.

1164
01:35:55.447 --> 01:35:57.407
<i>Let her die.</i>

1165
01:36:00.368 --> 01:36:02.955
DEMONIC VOICE [ON RECORDER]: <i>I am</i> no <i>one.
I</i> am no one.

1166
01:36:03.122 --> 01:36:04.415
<i>Fear the priest.</i>

1167
01:36:04.916 --> 01:36:06.250
[GROWL]

1168
01:36:06.417 --> 01:36:08.085
<i>Fear the priest.</i>

1169
01:36:10.797 --> 01:36:12.215
<i>Merrin!</i>

1170
01:36:15.009 --> 01:36:17.345
[TAPE REWINDING]

1171
01:36:19.931 --> 01:36:22.058
<i>I am no one.</i>

1172
01:36:24.435 --> 01:36:25.895
<i>Merrin! Fear the priest.</i>

1173
01:36:26.062 --> 01:36:27.772
[PHONE RINGING]

1174
01:36:27.939 --> 01:36:29.732
<i>Merrin!</i>

1175
01:36:30.316 --> 01:36:33.069
<i>Merrin!</i>

1176
01:36:33.653 --> 01:36:34.946
Yeah?

1177
01:36:36.572 --> 01:36:37.949
Yeah?

1178
01:36:39.200 --> 01:36:40.243
I'll be right there.

1179
01:36:58.762 --> 01:37:00.514
I don't want Chris to see this.

1180
01:37:00.681 --> 01:37:03.225
Well, what's wrong? What is it?
Shh.

1181
01:38:12.046 --> 01:38:14.381
You're convinced that it's genuine?

1182
01:38:14.924 --> 01:38:16.342
I don't know.

1183
01:38:17.509 --> 01:38:19.803
No, not really, I suppose.

1184
01:38:20.304 --> 01:38:22.348
But I have made...

1185
01:38:22.514 --> 01:38:26.894
a prudent judgment that it meets
the conditions set down in The Ritual.

1186
01:38:27.102 --> 01:38:29.563
You would want to do the exorcism
yourself?

1187
01:38:30.856 --> 01:38:32.107
Yes.

1188
01:38:35.903 --> 01:38:37.905
Might be best to have a man
with experience.

1189
01:38:38.072 --> 01:38:41.367
Maybe someone who's spent time
in foreign missions.

1190
01:38:42.034 --> 01:38:43.994
I understand, Your Excellency.

1191
01:38:44.453 --> 01:38:45.704
Let's see who's around.

1192
01:38:45.871 --> 01:38:49.042
In the meantime,
I'll call you as soon as I know.

1193
01:38:49.876 --> 01:38:52.170
Thank you, Your Excellency.

1194
01:38:52.545 --> 01:38:54.631
Well, he does know the background.

1195
01:38:54.798 --> 01:38:58.259
I doubt there's any danger in just
having him assist.

1196
01:38:58.426 --> 01:39:01.137
There should be a psychiatrist present,
anyway.

1197
01:39:01.304 --> 01:39:03.098
What about the exorcist?

1198
01:39:03.390 --> 01:39:04.808
Have you any ideas?

1199
01:39:05.850 --> 01:39:07.894
How about Lankester Merrin?

1200
01:39:08.353 --> 01:39:09.896
Merrin?

1201
01:39:10.188 --> 01:39:11.690
I had a notion he was in Iraq.

1202
01:39:11.856 --> 01:39:14.067
I read he was working on a dig
near Nineveh.

1203
01:39:14.234 --> 01:39:15.735
You're right, but he's finished.

1204
01:39:15.902 --> 01:39:19.406
He came back three or four months ago.
He's at Woodstock now.

1205
01:39:19.572 --> 01:39:21.241
What's he doing there, teaching?

1206
01:39:21.408 --> 01:39:23.994
He's working on another book.

1207
01:39:24.160 --> 01:39:28.040
Don't you think he's too old, Tom?
How's his health?

1208
01:39:28.374 --> 01:39:31.919
He must be all right.
He's still running around digging up tombs.

1209
01:39:32.545 --> 01:39:33.629
Mm.

1210
01:39:33.796 --> 01:39:37.341
Besides, he's had experience.
I didn't know that.

1211
01:39:37.550 --> 01:39:39.760
Ten, 12 years ago, I think, in Africa.

1212
01:39:39.927 --> 01:39:43.848
The exorcism supposedly lasted months.
I heard it damn near killed him.

1213
01:39:48.269 --> 01:39:49.645
Father?

1214
01:40:56.422 --> 01:40:58.508
You're Mrs. MacNeil?
Yes.

1215
01:40:58.674 --> 01:41:00.051
I'm Father Merrin.

1216
01:41:00.259 --> 01:41:02.553
Come in.
Thank you.

1217
01:41:03.137 --> 01:41:04.680
Is Father Karras here?
Yes.

1218
01:41:04.847 --> 01:41:06.891
He's here already.
Father?

1219
01:41:07.517 --> 01:41:10.520
Father Karras.
It's an honor to meet you, Father.

1220
01:41:10.686 --> 01:41:12.980
[DEMONIC VOICE SCREAMING]

1221
01:41:17.026 --> 01:41:19.112
Are you very tired?
No.

1222
01:41:20.363 --> 01:41:23.366
I'd like you to go quickly across
to the Residence, Damien...

1223
01:41:23.533 --> 01:41:25.368
and gather up a cassock for myself...

1224
01:41:25.535 --> 01:41:29.497
two surplices, a purple stole,
and some holy water...

1225
01:41:29.664 --> 01:41:31.207
and, um...

1226
01:41:31.542 --> 01:41:34.503
your copy of The Roman Ritual.
The large one.

1227
01:41:34.670 --> 01:41:36.380
I believe we should begin.

1228
01:41:36.880 --> 01:41:39.299
Do you want to hear the background
of the case first?

1229
01:41:39.466 --> 01:41:40.717
Why?

1230
01:41:41.218 --> 01:41:43.387
<i>MAN [ON RADIO]:
This is yours to do with as you please.</i>

1231
01:41:43.554 --> 01:41:47.141
<i>You can choose to escape, if you want,
but you may never be able to return.</i>

1232
01:41:47.307 --> 01:41:49.143
<i>Don't let anyone decide for you.</i>

1233
01:41:49.309 --> 01:41:52.312
[REGAN MOANING]

1234
01:42:02.114 --> 01:42:04.741
Hail Mary, full of grace...

1235
01:42:04.908 --> 01:42:06.910
[PRAYING INDISTINCTLY]

1236
01:42:17.630 --> 01:42:19.757
Excuse me.
Thank you.

1237
01:42:22.010 --> 01:42:23.595
Thank you very much.

1238
01:42:23.761 --> 01:42:25.180
You're welcome.

1239
01:42:35.481 --> 01:42:37.775
Would you like some brandy in that,
Father?

